-2 NAME~
NAME POLICY:
In order to create a role-playing and adventure atmosphere throughout the
Shades of Gray, you must choose a name accordingly explained below:
 
ACCEPTABLE:
1)  Proper names, medieval or modern. i.e  (Takasi, Mitra)
2)  Created names with a medieval or fictional sound.  (Priatros, Sansoles)
 
UNACCEPTABLE:                                                        
1)  Vulgar or sexually suggestive names.  (No examples needed)
2)  Nouns which are names of animals.  (Horse, Doll)          
3)  Strings of random characters.  (Asdfg, Qwdldkf)                
4)  Titles which imply rank or privelege.   (Lord, Sir,...)
5)  Scientific phrases, words. (Proof, Logic, Electrics...)
6)  Object names. (Necklace, Staff, Sword etc)              
7)  Compound names. (FarmerJoe, Maryjane etc.)
 
Anyway, immortals may ask you to choose another name if they consider your name inappropriate.

If your name fits above restrictions, type Y. Otherwise choose another name.
Last decision depend upon Immortals of Shades of Gray. Do you accept? ~
0 CAST~
Syntax: cast <spell> <target>

Before you can cast a spell, you have to practice it.  The more you practice,
the higher chance you have of success when casting.  Casting spells costs mana.
The mana cost decreases as your level increases.

The <target> is optional.  Many spells which need targets will use an
appropriate default target, especially during combat.

If the spell name is more than one word, then you must quote the spell name.
Example: cast 'cure critic' frag.  Quoting is optional for single-word spells.
You can abbreviate the spell name.

When you cast an offensive spell, the victim usually gets a saving throw.
The effect of the spell is reduced or eliminated if the victim makes the
saving throw successfully.

See also the help sections for individual spells.
~
